{
  "texts": [
    "While the discriminator model is used to classify examples as real (from the domain) or fake (generated).",
    "These two models compete against an enemy in a zero-sum game.",
    "Samples are created immediately by the generator.",
    "The discriminator, its rival, makes an effort to discriminate between samples taken from the generator and samples taken from the training data.",
    "The game continues until the generator model is producing believable examples and the discriminator model is duped roughly half the time [54]."
  ]
}